# Walkthrough: MediScan Secure Full System

The complete **MediScan Secure Full** suite is now running. This setup includes the main dashboard, the API backend, the specialized OCR service, and the legacy UI.

## Active Components & Ports

| Component | Technology | URL |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Vite UI** | React / Vite | [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080) |
| **Next.js Dashboard** | Next.js | [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) |
| **Backend API** | Node.js / Express | [http://localhost:3001](http://localhost:3001) |
| **OCR Service** | Python / FastAPI | [http://localhost:8085](http://localhost:8085) |

## How to Start the Full System

To start everything simultaneously, you need to run two separate sets of commands (one for Node/Web and one for Python/OCR).

### 1. Start the Monorepo (Web, API, UI)
From the root directory:
```bash
npm run dev
```
*This command uses Turbo to launch `apps/web` (3000), `apps/api` (3001), and `elysian-health-ui-main` (8080) in parallel.*

### 2. Start the OCR Service
From the root directory in a **new terminal**:
```bash
cd update_for_ocr
uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8085
```

> [!TIP]
> Each service has been tested and verified as accessible. The Vite UI on port 8080 is configured to proxy API requests to port 3001 automatically.
